                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ws8j65r/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>equal not being able to keep my religion as I<lb/> properly should it might be said I\n                have no<lb/> right to find fault, but bad as I may be in<lb/> not following the\n                precepts as laid down I am &amp;<lb/> have <sic>allways</sic> been an anti reformist\n                in any<lb/> shape &amp; will never give my consent to any change<lb/> no matter how\n                small. I feel that to change<lb/> any one portion of our forms destroys the\n                whole,<lb/> &amp; the more I read your <sic>excellant</sic> Book the<lb/> stronger\n                my conviction, but enough I am not<lb/> qualified to write on this grave subject\n                in<lb/> a short time you shall hear from wishing<lb/> you health &amp; happiness I\n                Remain</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(7)\">Yours very truly</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(8)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">M. N. Nathan</persName>\n            </p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ws8j65r/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
